A vintage 1950s-style illustration of a detective with a magnifying glass peering into an elaborate filing cabinet system that stretches endlessly in all directions, drawers open at various angles revealing colorful folders and documents. The scene has warm sepia and amber tones with mint green and coral accents. The cabinet morphs organically like a maze, with some drawers connecting through impossible geometric angles. Dust motes float in dramatic diagonal light beams streaming through an unseen window. The detective's silhouette is stylized and elegant, wearing a fedora, captured mid-discovery with an expression of triumph. The composition suggests the satisfaction of finding exactly what you're looking for among vast archives.
